## Commands

```bash
npm install          # Install dependencies
npm run dev          # Start dev server
npm run build        # Production build
npm test             # Run test suite
npm run lint         # Lint check
npm run lint:fix     # Auto-fix lint issues
npm run format       # Format code
npm run format:check # Check formatting
```

## Architecture

- `src/` — Application source code
  - `utils/` — Pure utility functions (one per file, re-export via index.ts)
  - `services/` — External integrations (one per file)
  - `models/` — Types/interfaces (one per file)
  - `lib/` — Internal shared logic
- `tests/` — Test files (mirror src/ structure)

## Code Style

- ES modules (`import`/`export`), not CommonJS (`require`)
- TypeScript strict mode
- One function/class per file in utils/, services/, models/
- Max 50 lines per function, max 200 lines per file (enforced by ESLint)
- Barrel re-exports via index.ts in each directory

## Testing

- Framework: Vitest
- Run single test: `npx vitest run tests/path/test.ts`
- Mirror src/ structure in tests/
- Use shared fixtures from `tests/setup.ts`
- No mocks unless testing external services

## Security

This repo is public. Never write actual values from `~/.env` into any file. Use env var names, `process.env.VAR`, or `<placeholder>` syntax. Use generic names (alice, bob) not real names. Use `localhost` or `<host>` not real IPs. Hookify rules and gitleaks pre-commit enforce this.

